I made reservations for a surprise birthday party for my wife and when I arrived to the restaurant the hostess in front of my wife immediately ruined the surprise by stating the rest of the party was inside this was the first of many many more parts of horrible service. The waiter came to our table took half the tables order then came back 20 minutes later to take the other half of the tables order, being that it was my wife’s birthday party she was the last not 1st to be asked what she would like to eat. Once the dinner started to come out everyone was being given someone else’s plate, I ordered the lobster cavelli (which was actually good) but steak was placed in front of me, it was a party of 10 and only 2 of the guest received their correct plate, causing us to have to reach over one another to recover our plates. When this happened I requested to speak to the manager Fabio Palomba, once he came to the table he tapped me on the shoulder and said “What is it that you need?” No introduction, extremely distant and passive aggressive. Once I explained my concerns with the service he shrugs his shoulders and say “ok I’m sorry but what else would you want me to do” extremely dismissive of my concerns and quite frankly unapologetic. He walked away and for the rest of the night continued to watch and mock our table with the waiters by pointing and laughing. Due to me being upset a friend of ours chose to go speak with the manager, she also stated that he was unapologetic with the service but would send us a shot of liquor to make everything alright. I took offense to this gesture as I felt like he pretty much stereo typed our group as young African Americans who can be bought by given liquor so that we can shut up. We as a group decided not to touch the shots. The restaurant was highly recommended but after this experience I would never recommend a friend to go eat at ‘SWAN’.
